/************
Color Mixer:
The colors red, blue, and yellow are known as the primary colors because they cannot be made by mixing other colors.
When you mix two primary colors, you get a secondary color, as shown here: 

- When you mix red and blue, you get purple
- When you mix red and yellow you get orange.
- When you mix blue and yellow, you get green. 

Design a program that prompts the user to enter the names of two primary colors to mix.  if the user enters anything other than "red," "blue," or "yellow," the program should display an error message.  Otherwise, the program should display the name of the secondary color that results. 
*************/

Pseucod Code: 
Module main() 
                     
	Declare String firstColor
	Declare String secondColor

	Display "Enter your first color: " 
	Input firstColor

	Display "Enter your second color: " 
	Input secondColor

	Call  calculateSecondaryColor(String Val firstColor, String Val secondColor, String Ref newColor) 

End Module()


Call  calculateSecondaryColor(String Val firstColor, String Val secondColor, String Ref newColor) 

Declare String newColor

If firstColor == red AND secondColor == blue Then
	Set newColor = purple
	Display "You Get: ", newColor 
	Else 
		if firstColor == red AND secondColor == yellow Then 
			Set newColor = orange
			Display "You get: ", newColor 
		Else
			if firstColor == blue AND secondColor = yellow Then
				Set newColor = green
				Display "You Get: ", newColor 
			Else
				Display "Error"
			End If
		End If 
	End If
End if 	
End Module() 
